  <!-- ─── INSTALL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="section" id="install">
    <h2>Install</h2>
    <p class="lead-2">Two runtimes, two recipes. Both leave the <code>.cms</code> source alone.</p>

    <div class="snippet-grid">
      <div>
        <h3>cms-vercel</h3>
        <p>One option in <code>api/index.ts</code>:</p>
<pre><code>import { createHandler } from 'cms-vercel';

export default createHandler({
  ui: 'pro',  // theme + enhancers
});
</code></pre>
        <p>The runtime injects the link / script tags into the default shell.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>.NET runtime (CaseMaster.Web.exe)</h3>
        <p>Append two snippets to your app's <code>static/css/app.css</code> and <code>static/js/app.js</code>:</p>
<pre><code>/* app.css */
@import url('/static/lib/prism/prism.min.css');
</code></pre>
<pre><code>// app.js
const s = document.createElement('script');
s.type = 'module';
s.src  = '/static/lib/prism/prism.js';
document.body.appendChild(s);
</code></pre>
        <p>Survives <code>git pull</code> of the framework. Vendored or CDN, your call.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

